sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1913028
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Wild type ptet-FixK2 hybrid promoter with mRFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pltet-FixK2 hybrid promoter composite part includes mRFP reporter (BBa_E1010). After co-transformation with light sensor BBa_K1913033, mRFP fluorescence could be detected after 12h culture.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tianhe Wang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Genomic sequence of Bradyrhizobium japonicum, iGEM part registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In order to test wild type ptet-FixK2 hybrid promoter,we put reporter mRFP under this promoter and co-transformed with light sensor BBa_K1913034. And mRFP fluorescence value was tested so that the intensity of transcription of this promoter could be quantified.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1913026
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Wild type ptet-FixK2 hybrid promoter is the promoter that could not only be activated by light sensorsYF1-FixJ composite and but inhibited by TetR repressor. The sequence of upper control element and core element region are from wild type FixK2 hybrid promoter on genomic sequence of Bradyrhizobium japonicum. Additional tet operators are inserted in the core element region of promoter as second control element that results in transcription repression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tianhe Wang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In order to make Fixk2 promoter as an inducible promoter for the toggle switch, we had to add additional repressor operator sequences into the Fixk2 sequence, they are both inserted in the core element region of the Fixk2 sequence, which could be bonded by dimerized TetR repressors resulting in the formation of steric hindrance and consequently on transcription repression.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
